Class ScfChromatogramBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jcvi.jillion.trace.chromat.scf.ScfChromatogramBuilder

    public final class ScfChromatogramBuilder
extends Object

    SCFChromatogramBuilder uses the Builder pattern to create a new ScfChromatogram instance.

      • ScfChromatogramBuilder

        public ScfChromatogramBuilder(String id)
        Create a new ScfChromatogramBuilder instance with all fields except for the id unset. In order to successfully build a valid ScfChromatogram object please use the various setter methods in this class to set everything before calling build().
        Parameters:
        id - the id for this Chromatogram object to have; can not be null.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if either field is null.

      • ScfChromatogramBuilder

        public ScfChromatogramBuilder(String id,
                              File scfFile)
                       throws IOException
        Create a new ScfChromatogramBuilder instance with the given id and all fields initially set to the the values encoded in the given scf file.
        Parameters:
        id - the id for this Chromatogram object to have; can not be null.
        scfFile - a SCF encoded file that contains the initial values that this builder should have; can not be null.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem reading the file or if the given file is not a valid scf encoded file.
        NullPointerException - if either field is null.

      • ScfChromatogramBuilder

        public ScfChromatogramBuilder(String id,
                              InputStream scfInputStream)
                       throws IOException
        Create a new ScfChromatogramBuilder instance with the given id and all fields initially set to the the values encoded in the given scf encoded inputStream. The InputStream will NOT be closed by this constructor, client code must close the stream themselves after returning from this method (preferably in a finally block).
        Parameters:
        id - the id for this Chromatogram object to have; can not be null.
        scfInputStream - a SCF encoded InputStream that contains the initial values that this builder should have; can not be null.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem reading the file or if the InputStream does not contain valid scf encoded data.
        NullPointerException - if either field is null.

      • ScfChromatogramBuilder

        public ScfChromatogramBuilder(Chromatogram copy)
        Create a new instance of ScfChromatogramBuilder using the given Chromatogram instance to set all the initial fields. Only the fields in the Chromatogram interface will be copied, any scf specific fields will be null. Use the various scf specific setter methods to set those values.
        Parameters:
        copy - a Chromatogram object whose fields are used as the initial values of this new Builder; can not be null;
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if copy is null.
